perf(brightness): persistent Python daemon, overlay fade, IPC errors

Replace per-call Python subprocess with a persistent brightness daemon:
- Python process stays alive, receives JSON commands over stdin/stdout
- Eliminates ~300ms process spawn overhead per brightness call
- Heartbeat every 10s with auto-respawn if daemon dies
- Watchdog kills and restarts after 3 missed heartbeats

Add overlay fade transitions:
- 100ms ease-out fade-in when overlays appear
- 100ms ease-in fade-out before overlay windows close
- Smoother perceived quality when switching profiles

Add IPC error result types:
- setBrightness now returns { ok, error? } instead of void
- BrightnessResult interface for typed error handling
- IpcResult shared type for future IPC error patterns
- Daemon errors surface with descriptive messages

Bundle daemon script via extraResources for packaged builds.
